WEBVTT

00:01.234 --> 00:03.370
I'M WAYNE MALLOY.
MY FAMILY AND I ARE TRAVELLERS.

00:03.404 --> 00:06.974
OUR KIND HAS BEEN
LIVING IN THIS COUNTRY
FOR 150 YEARS.

00:07.008 --> 00:10.311
WE'RE NOT LISTED
IN THE PHONE BOOK. WE DON'T
HAVE SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBERS.

00:10.344 --> 00:11.312
WE LIVE OFF THE GRID.

00:11.345 --> 00:14.849
SOME CALL US GYPSIES.
OTHERS CALL US THIEVES.

00:14.882 --> 00:17.919
‐ CAEL!
‐ MOST, THOUGH,
DON'T EVEN KNOW WE EXIST.

00:17.952 --> 00:23.658
I'VE GOT THREE KIDS:
A BOY, A GIRL AND, UM‐‐

00:23.691 --> 00:26.828
MY WIFE, DAHLIA,
IS JUST OUT OF JAIL ON PAROLE.

00:26.861 --> 00:29.230
WE TOOK HER HOME
TO THE TRAVELLER CAMP.

00:29.263 --> 00:31.599
THE FAMILY GAVE HER
A WARM WELCOME.

00:31.633 --> 00:34.268
‐ OH.
‐ I, ON THE OTHER HAND, GOT
A DIFFERENT TYPE OF WELCOME.

00:34.301 --> 00:37.104
I AM THE NEW BOSS.
HE IS THE OLD BOSS.

00:37.138 --> 00:39.841
‐ [ Bell Ringing ]
‐ GET OVER IT.

00:39.874 --> 00:43.578
[ Wayne Narrating ] SOMETIMES
IT TAKES A BEATING TO MAKE YOU
REALIZE IT'S TIME TO M
OVE ON.

00:43.611 --> 00:45.613
SO WHERE ARE WE GONNA GO?

00:47.815 --> 00:51.252
LIFE'S A RIVER, KID.
YOU GOTTA GO WHERE
IT TAKES YOU.

00:51.285 --> 00:53.955
[ Wayne Narrating ]
SO, WITH A LOAN FROM
THE FAMILY BANK,

00:53.988 --> 00:57.859
I PACKED UP THE R. V.
AND WENT OUT IN SEARCH OF
SOMETHING BETTER,

00:57.892 --> 00:59.761
SOMETHING WE COULD
ALL BE PROUD OF.
[ Linda ] WAYNE!

00:59.794 --> 01:02.296
SOMETHING WITH
A BIT MORE SUBSTANCE.

01:02.329 --> 01:04.431
LOOK, DALE AND I
HAD A DISAGREEMENT.

01:04.465 --> 01:06.200
‐ [ Dahlia ]
...GODDAMN BIRTHSTONE!
‐ TAKE 'EM OFF!

01:06.233 --> 01:08.636
[ Wayne Narrating ]
IT WASN'T THAT LONG BEFORE
THE FAMILY TRIED TO STOP US.

01:08.670 --> 01:11.205
WRONG LANE, ASSHOLE!
MICK! LOOK OUT!

01:11.238 --> 01:14.441
[ Linda ]
SHIT. STOP!

01:14.475 --> 01:18.379
[ Wayne Narrating ]
UNFORTUNATELY, THEY STOPPED
SOMEONE ELSE INSTEAD.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.014
AND THEN THEY RAN.

01:26.153 --> 01:30.224
KNOWING THAT WE COULDN'T GO BACK
TO OUR OLD HOME, WE DECIDED
TO VISIT THEIR NEW HOME,

01:30.257 --> 01:33.460
EDENFALLS,
AS THE RICHES.

01:33.494 --> 01:35.563
[ Dahlia ]
NOW, WHO BUYS A HOUSE
ON THE INTERNET?

01:35.597 --> 01:37.899
‐ COME AND MEET
OUR NEW NEIGHBORS.
‐ DOUG, MEET HUGH PANETTA,

01:37.932 --> 01:40.602
‐ BIGGEST ASSHOLE
EAST OF THE MISSISSIPPI.
‐ [ Chuckles ]

01:40.635 --> 01:43.505
‐ YOU FLATTER ME, JIM.
‐ YOU'RE SLEEPIN' OUT HERE, HUH?

01:43.538 --> 01:45.807
YEAH.
[ Wayne Narrating ]
I'M PROUD TO SAY...

01:45.840 --> 01:50.344
MY FAMILY IS FINALLY ON THE GRID
AND SURROUNDED BY SUBSTANCE.

01:50.377 --> 01:52.914
I'VE TAKEN MANY THINGS
IN MY LIFE,

01:52.947 --> 01:56.350
BUT I'M ON MY WAY
TO TAKING SOMETHING
I NEVER THOUGHT POSSIBLE.

01:57.952 --> 02:00.955
[ Wayne's Voice ]
THE AMERICAN DREAM.
WE'RE GONNA STEAL IT.

02:13.568 --> 02:16.470
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
PRACTICING.

02:18.540 --> 02:20.608
PRACTICING WHAT?

02:20.642 --> 02:22.544
BEING HER.

02:24.411 --> 02:26.480
WHY DON'T YOU COME PRACTICE
BEING HER WITH ME?

02:26.514 --> 02:29.283
YOU WANT TO DO IT
LIKE A BUFFER, WAYNE?

02:29.316 --> 02:31.853
OH, YOU KNOW
HOW BUFFERS DO IT?

02:31.886 --> 02:34.822
HOW?
ONCE A YEAR, IN A CAVE,

02:34.856 --> 02:37.792
STANDING UP LIKE POLAR BEARS.

02:37.825 --> 02:40.695
[ Laughs ]
POLAR BEARS?
YEAH. THAT'S IT.

02:40.728 --> 02:43.130
I THINK THEY FAKE IT.
WHAT, A POLAR BEAR?

02:43.164 --> 02:45.667
A LOT. OH!

02:45.700 --> 02:48.169
I WANNA FAKE IT, WAYNE.

02:48.202 --> 02:50.505
I WANNA FAKE IT
LIKE A BUFFER.
OH!

02:50.538 --> 02:53.641
OH, WAYNE! WAYNE!
MMM! MMM!

02:53.675 --> 02:56.711
OH, GODDAMN IT, WAYNE!

02:56.744 --> 02:58.746
OH!

03:12.560 --> 03:14.596
[ Sighs ]

03:14.629 --> 03:16.631
[ Crickets Chirping ]

03:25.707 --> 03:27.709
[ Beeping ]

03:30.377 --> 03:32.747
[ Cael ]
IT'S ME.
WHERE ARE YOU?

03:32.780 --> 03:35.349
I CAN'T SAY.

03:35.382 --> 03:37.585
FAR.

03:37.619 --> 03:39.621
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
SAY GOOD‐BYE.

03:41.623 --> 03:43.691
COULDN'T.

03:43.725 --> 03:46.093
WHEN AM I EVER
GONNA SEE YOU AGAIN?

03:47.762 --> 03:49.797
I DON'T KNOW.

03:49.831 --> 03:52.399
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT WE'RE DOIN' HERE.

03:55.269 --> 03:57.939
I MISS YOU.
[ Woman ]
TAMMY!

03:57.972 --> 04:01.743
SHIT. MA'S COMIN'.
I GOTTA GO.
I LOVE YOU.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.527
[ Buzzing ]

04:21.295 --> 04:23.831
OH.

04:23.865 --> 04:27.602
MAN'S GETTIN' CALLS IN
THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT, BABY.
CAN'T BE A GOOD THING.

04:27.635 --> 04:30.505
MAYBE IT'S ED McMAHON.

04:30.538 --> 04:32.607
MAYBE DOUG'S ALREADY A WINNER.

04:32.640 --> 04:36.377
DON'T BE STUPID.
ED McMAHON DON'T CALL.
HE'D COME TO THE HOUSE.

04:37.779 --> 04:39.747
PROMISE ME
YOU WON'T ANSWER THIS.

04:39.781 --> 04:41.749
BABY, I‐‐
PROMISE ME.

04:41.783 --> 04:44.185
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT. OW.

04:45.553 --> 04:48.022
[ Inhales, Exhales Deeply ]

04:53.628 --> 04:55.530
WE CAN DO THIS.

04:56.531 --> 04:58.700
PEOPLE DO IT ALL THE TIME.

04:58.733 --> 05:02.136
OH, THEY DO?

05:02.169 --> 05:06.508
THEY MOVE INTO DEAD PEOPLE'S
HOUSES, STEAL ALL THEIR STUFF
AND PRETEND TO BE THEM?

05:06.541 --> 05:10.044
BABY, THIS‐‐ ALL THIS‐‐
IS MANIFEST DESTINY.

05:10.077 --> 05:12.947
IT'S MEANT TO BE.

05:12.980 --> 05:14.982
YOU'RE MY QUEEN, BABY.

05:16.183 --> 05:18.152
BUT, WAYNE,

05:18.185 --> 05:20.487
WHAT IF I LIKE IT?

05:26.260 --> 05:28.462
NOTHING WRONG
WITH LIKING IT.

05:28.495 --> 05:30.632
WHEN I WAS A GIRL,

05:30.665 --> 05:32.667
I ALWAYS WANTED
TO GO TO A PROM,

05:32.700 --> 05:35.670
WEAR ONE OF THEM
BIG OLD FANCY DRESSES.

05:36.938 --> 05:40.174
HAVE SOME OF THOSE‐‐
WHAT YOU CALL 'EM?

05:40.207 --> 05:42.176
SHOES?

05:42.209 --> 05:44.178
[ Giggles ]
YOU ASSHOLE.

05:44.211 --> 05:46.180
NO, ONE OF THEM
FLOWER THINGS.

05:47.414 --> 05:49.383
THINK OF THE LIFE
WE CAN HAVE.

05:49.416 --> 05:51.418
THINK OF THE KIDS.

05:52.720 --> 05:54.689
IT'S NOT REAL, WAYNE.

05:54.722 --> 05:57.424
WE CAN MAKE IT REAL.

05:57.458 --> 05:59.827
HMM.

05:59.861 --> 06:01.929
I'M GONNA GO
CHECK ON THE KIDS.

06:17.745 --> 06:19.747
OKAY.

06:22.550 --> 06:27.755
THREE, FOUR, FIVE,
SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

06:27.789 --> 06:29.757
OKAY.

06:29.791 --> 06:33.460
EIGHT FROM THE DOOR
AND TO THE LEFT OF THE TREE.

06:35.797 --> 06:37.799
[ Grunting ]

06:40.067 --> 06:41.803
[ Buzzing ]

07:19.807 --> 07:22.744
[ Garbage Disposal Whirring ]
WHERE DO YOU THINK
IT ALL GOES?

07:22.777 --> 07:26.914
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW, SAM,
BUT IT SURE DOES MAKE
A LOT OF NOISE GETTIN' THERE.

07:26.948 --> 07:29.951
[ Grinding ]
STOP IT, SAM.

07:29.984 --> 07:32.987
THIS GUY'S GOT
CRAP TASTE IN MUSIC,
BUT HE'S GOT COOL SHIT.

07:33.020 --> 07:35.489
[ Dahlia ]
HEY. LISTEN TO THIS.
"WHEN YOU FOLLOW YOUR BLISS,

07:35.523 --> 07:38.760
"DOORS WILL APPEAR WHERE
THERE WOULD NOT HAVE BEEN...

07:38.793 --> 07:41.929
DOORS BEFORE AND
WHERE THERE WOULDN'T BE
DOORS FOR ANYONE ELSE."

07:41.963 --> 07:44.599
‐ WHAT THE HELL DOES THAT MEAN?
‐ [ Cael ] I THINK IT'S WHAT
WE'RE DOIN' HERE.

07:44.632 --> 07:47.434
‐ WHAT? BLISS?
‐ [ Sam ]
WHAT'S BLISS?

07:47.468 --> 07:49.470
BLISS IS PASSION.

07:49.504 --> 07:52.940
IF YOU LIVE YOUR LIFE WITH
PASSION, FORTUNE FOLLOWS YOU.

07:52.974 --> 07:55.777
YEAH. IT WORKS REAL WELL
IF IT'S IN A HOUSE
BEHIND A BIG‐ASS GATE.

07:55.810 --> 07:58.345
[ Wayne ]
MAYBE. MAYBE WE'RE
FOLLOWING OUR BLISS.

07:58.379 --> 08:01.549
OKAY. LISTEN UP, TEAM.
WE GOT A LOT TO DO TODAY.

08:01.583 --> 08:03.585
[ Doorbell Rings ]

08:07.655 --> 08:09.957
‐ [ Knocks ]
‐ [ Gasps ]

08:09.991 --> 08:12.393
‐ SAJICK!
‐ SHIT, DAD.

08:12.426 --> 08:14.495
ALL RIGHT. SPLIT UP. HEY, NO.
YOU GUYS STAY TOGETHER.

08:14.529 --> 08:17.364
HEY! NO, NO.
STEASH! STOP!

08:18.365 --> 08:20.334
THE RICHES ARE
LAW‐ABIDING CITIZENS.

08:20.367 --> 08:23.971
EVERYONE STAY WHERE YOU ARE.
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

08:24.005 --> 08:25.740
HIDE.

08:33.014 --> 08:34.982
MORNING, OFFICER.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.083
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

08:39.086 --> 08:41.655
MR. RICH?
MR. DOUGLAS RICH?

08:41.688 --> 08:44.225
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

08:44.258 --> 08:46.227
WELL, THAT DEPENDS ON
WHAT YOU CALL A PROBLEM.

08:48.295 --> 08:50.865
I NOTICE YOU DON'T
HAVE A SYSTEM.

08:50.898 --> 08:53.400
A SYSTEM?

08:53.434 --> 08:55.737
AN ALARM SYSTEM.

08:57.739 --> 09:01.408
OFFICER LLOYD SHRAGE.
SPARTAN SECURITY.

09:02.476 --> 09:04.445
I WOULD LIKE TO
WELCOME YOU...

09:04.478 --> 09:07.114
AND CONGRATULATE YOU ON
MOVING TO THE SAFEST
COMMUNITY IN LOUISIANA.

09:07.148 --> 09:11.185
UH‐‐ [ Stammers ]
THANK YOU VERY MUCH,
OFFICER.

09:11.218 --> 09:14.421
I AM SO GLAD TO, UH‐‐
TO HEAR THAT.

09:14.455 --> 09:16.524
UH, MY FAMILY'S
VERY PRECIOUS TO ME.

09:16.558 --> 09:19.426
AT SPARTAN, WE PROVIDE FOR ALL
OUR RESIDENTS' SECURITY NEEDS‐‐

09:19.460 --> 09:22.697
ALARM SYSTEMS, 24‐HOUR PATROL
DISPATCH AND ARMED PATROL.

09:22.730 --> 09:25.032
OH. WELL ARMED?

09:25.066 --> 09:27.969
YOU BET.
WE ALL CARRY ASSAULT WEAPONS.

09:28.002 --> 09:30.071
NO SHIT.
WELL, YOU‐ALL
GET SETTLED IN,

09:30.104 --> 09:32.073
AND YOU GIVE US A CALL.

09:32.106 --> 09:34.075
'CAUSE YOU CAN'T BE
TOO CAREFUL THESE DAYS.

09:34.108 --> 09:37.879
NO, I NOTICED THAT. SO, UH,
YEAH. I WILL DO THIS.

09:37.912 --> 09:40.381
OFFICER SHRAGE.
EXCELLENT.

09:40.414 --> 09:42.850
ARMED WEAPONS.
KEEP 'EM LOCKED AND LOADED.

09:44.251 --> 09:46.253
GOOD.

09:50.825 --> 09:52.827
[ Breathes Deeply ]

09:57.298 --> 09:59.534
EASY‐PEASY JAPANESEY.

10:00.602 --> 10:02.103
HELLO?

10:03.437 --> 10:06.107
YOU PEOPLE
HAVE GOT TO RELAX.

10:06.140 --> 10:09.944
BUFFERS ARE NOT
AFRAID OF COPS.
COPS ARE OUR FRIENDS.

10:09.977 --> 10:12.113
WHAT IF THAT
HAD BEEN A COP?

10:12.146 --> 10:14.516
WHAT IF THAT HAD BEEN
SOMEONE COMIN' TO FIND THEM?

10:14.549 --> 10:17.519
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS
IF THEY FIND US?
YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENS TO ME?

10:17.552 --> 10:21.589
I GO BACK TO PRISON.
YOU GO TO PRISON.
KIDS GO TO FOSTER HOMES.

10:21.623 --> 10:23.625
YOU WANT THAT?

10:30.464 --> 10:32.667
WE RUN IF WE HAVE TO.

10:43.578 --> 10:45.613
SOMEHOW YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TRUST ME.

10:45.647 --> 10:47.248
OH, I HEARD THAT BEFORE.

10:50.985 --> 10:53.521
OKAY.

10:53.555 --> 10:56.290
SO LISTEN UP, TROOPS.

10:56.323 --> 11:00.294
WE'RE GONNA DIG INTO THESE
BUFFERS' LIVES UNTIL IT BLEEDS.

11:00.327 --> 11:04.566
I WANT TO KNOW ABOUT THEIR
FRIENDS, THEIR FAMILIES,
THEIR JOBS, THEIR HAT SIZE.

11:04.599 --> 11:07.201
CAEL, GET INTO
THOSE GADGETS, PLEASE.

11:07.234 --> 11:11.205
JUST GET THOSE MESSAGES.
READ THOSE E‐MAILS.
WILL YOU DO THAT?

11:11.238 --> 11:13.207
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
VERY KIND.

11:13.240 --> 11:16.310
DI DI, GRAB THAT BIG
LAUNDRY BASKET FULL OF MAIL...

11:16.343 --> 11:19.013
AND PULL OUT ANY
PREAPPROVED CREDIT CARD
APPLICATIONS.

11:19.046 --> 11:21.849
‐ DOUGIE'S GONNA NEED
SOME NEW CREDIT CARDS.
‐ OKAY.

11:21.883 --> 11:23.885
‐ UM‐‐
‐ WHAT CAN I DO, DAD?

11:23.918 --> 11:27.354
SAMMY, I WANT YOU TO GET
MY BAG OF TRICKS AND MAKE US
OUT SOME NEW I. D.'s, OKAY?

11:27.388 --> 11:29.356
OKAY.

11:29.390 --> 11:33.194
BABY, IF YOU COULD GET
DOUG'S CALENDAR, HERS TOO.

11:33.227 --> 11:37.732
JUST FIND OUT ANY RELATIVES,
FRIENDS, THINGS ABOUT THAT,
ANY STUFF.

11:37.765 --> 11:39.701
SEX SLAVES. WHATEVER.

11:41.302 --> 11:45.372
AND ANYBODY WHO DOES
GOOD WORK GETS TO SHOVE
SOMETHING DOWN THE SINK.

11:45.406 --> 11:48.543
TRY "RICH" WITH TWO R's.
ALREADY DID. NO GO.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.747
HONESTLY, WHO SPENDS $450
ON ONE PAIR OF SHOES?

11:52.780 --> 11:56.618
TRY "REALLY RICH GUY."
AND SHE BUYS
THREE OR FOUR AT A TIME.

11:56.651 --> 11:58.620
I KNOW, AND EVERY
ONE OF THEM BUTT UGLY.

11:58.653 --> 12:00.354
SERIOUSLY.
NO TASTE.

12:00.387 --> 12:03.190
TRY "RICH DEAD GUY."
SURPRISINGLY, NO.

12:03.224 --> 12:05.927
WHAT DATE IS IT TODAY?
UH,

12:05.960 --> 12:09.531
IT'S THE 23rd.
[ Dahlia ]
OKAY.

12:09.564 --> 12:11.533
WELL, YESTERDAY
WAS APPARENTLY...

12:11.566 --> 12:15.136
‐ HIS SECRETARY'S BIRTHDAY.
‐ [ Phone Beeping ]

12:15.169 --> 12:17.872
ARE YOU‐‐ YES! OW!

12:17.905 --> 12:21.475
WELL, HI THERE.
IS THIS THE JAVITZ HAIR SALON?

12:21.509 --> 12:23.978
NO? YOU'RE A LAW FIRM?

12:24.011 --> 12:25.713
OKAY. WELL,
I HAVE THE WRONG NUMBER.

12:25.747 --> 12:28.182
SILLY ME. BYE.
[ Beeps ]

12:29.250 --> 12:31.185
GOT IT.

12:33.154 --> 12:36.658
DOUG IS A REPUBLICAN.
HIS BEST FRIEND IS PETE.

12:36.691 --> 12:39.894
PETE'S A MORTGAGE BROKER
FROM DALLAS. HE'S E‐MAILED TWICE
ABOUT A GOLF TRIP,

12:39.927 --> 12:41.663
AND DOUG IS WAITING FOR
BIG MOMMA'S HOUSE 2 ON NETFLIX.

12:41.696 --> 12:43.898
DAMN, I'M GOOD.

12:43.931 --> 12:46.568
WELL DONE. OKAY. UH,
E‐MAIL HIM STRAIGHT BACK.

12:46.601 --> 12:49.737
UH, TELL HIM YOU GOT
A CONTAGIOUS DISEASE‐‐
ILLNESS.

12:49.771 --> 12:51.072
[ Dahlia ]
MONO.
CHLAMYDIA.

12:51.105 --> 12:55.176
FUN BUT FEMALE.
OKAY. MONO. MONO.

12:55.209 --> 12:57.111
AND SIGN IT
THE WAY DOUG WOULD.
"WEASEL."

12:58.012 --> 12:59.847
WOULD I MAKE THAT UP?

13:01.783 --> 13:03.785
[ Chattering ]

13:05.620 --> 13:07.622
[ Sighs ]

13:12.527 --> 13:14.529
[ Beeps ]

13:16.463 --> 13:18.465
SHIT.

13:21.468 --> 13:23.971
DAMN IT.
[ Engine Starts ]

13:24.005 --> 13:26.073
WHERE YOU GOIN', TAMMY?

13:35.382 --> 13:38.620
‐ WHAT THE HELL?
GET OUT THE WAY.
‐ NO.

13:38.653 --> 13:41.789
‐ MOVE YOUR ASS!
‐ I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE UP TO.
I'M GOIN' WITH YOU.

13:41.823 --> 13:43.825
THE HELL YOU ARE.

13:49.997 --> 13:51.999
I'M NOT HAPPY, DALE.

13:52.033 --> 13:55.369
YOU PROMISED A MARRIAGE FOR KEN.
WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM DOIN',
GINNY DANNEGAN?

13:55.402 --> 13:57.471
YOU'RE FOLLOWIN' TAMMY SIMMS.
I KNOW ABOUT HER AND CAEL.

13:57.505 --> 13:59.473
OH, YEAH?
I KNOW EVERYTHING.

13:59.507 --> 14:03.578
YOU DON'T KNOW SHIT.
[ Laughs ] I KNOW WAYNE MALLOY
STOLE THE FAMILY BANK.

14:03.611 --> 14:07.715
I KNOW THAT YOU ARE UP TO
YOUR EYEBALLS IN SHIT IF
YOU DON'T GET THAT MONEY BACK.

14:09.350 --> 14:13.087
I KNOW NONE OF THIS
IS HELPING YOUR POSITION HERE.
I KNOW ALL THAT.

14:14.421 --> 14:16.858
GET OUT.
NO.

14:16.891 --> 14:20.828
GET OUT OF MY TRUCK!

14:20.862 --> 14:22.163
AAAH!

14:22.196 --> 14:24.732
AAAH! LET‐‐

14:24.766 --> 14:27.502
‐ [ Grunts ]
‐ LET GO OF ME.

14:27.535 --> 14:29.771
LET GO OF ME. YOU HOG!

14:29.804 --> 14:33.407
SORRY EXCUSE FOR A MAN.

14:33.440 --> 14:37.444
[ Groans ]
I AM PREGNANT,

14:37.478 --> 14:39.246
ASSHOLE.
EASY, DALE.

14:39.280 --> 14:42.383
YOU OKAY, GINNY?
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.952
OH, GODDAMN IT.

14:44.986 --> 14:46.788
I LOST HER.

14:46.821 --> 14:48.122
[ Laughs ]

14:48.155 --> 14:50.424
THAT'S REAL NICE,
HITTIN' A PREGNANT WOMAN.

14:50.457 --> 14:53.227
WHAT DID YOU SAY TO ME?
NOTHIN'. DICKHEAD.

14:54.095 --> 14:56.130
[ Groans ]

14:56.163 --> 14:58.900
AAAH! YOU BROKE MY LEG.
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

15:00.067 --> 15:03.270
GOD! BROKE MY LEG!

15:03.304 --> 15:07.208
[ Mocking Groan ]
PUSSY.
[ Groans ]

15:07.241 --> 15:09.376
[ Engine Starts ]
GODDAMN IT.

15:09.410 --> 15:12.547
DOUG RICH WAS A LITIGATOR.

15:12.580 --> 15:14.716
A SECURITIES LAWYER,
WHATEVER THAT IS.

15:14.749 --> 15:17.084
CHERIEN WAS
HIS DENTAL HYGIENIST.

15:17.118 --> 15:20.555
THEY FELL IN LOVE
DURING A GUM SCRAPING
AND WERE MARRIED TWO YEARS AGO.

15:20.588 --> 15:23.424
IN TAMPA.
TOOK A LONG HONEYMOON
AROUND THE WORLD.

15:23.457 --> 15:26.160
KEPT A BLOG OF THEIR TRIP.
DOUG DOESN'T SEEM TO HAVE
TOO MANY FRIENDS,

15:26.193 --> 15:29.163
EXCEPT THAT GUY PETE, WHO
GAVE THE TOAST AT HIS WEDDING
VIDEO, SO HE COULD BE TROU
BLE.

15:29.196 --> 15:31.833
‐ CHERIEN?
‐ CHERIEN'S DAD IS DEAD,

15:31.866 --> 15:33.835
AND HER MA'S IN
A NURSING HOME IN BILOXI.

15:33.868 --> 15:36.070
OKAY. APART FROM PETE,

15:36.103 --> 15:38.239
NOT GONNA HAVE MUCH TROUBLE
FROM FAMILY OR FRIENDS.

15:38.272 --> 15:42.910
SO IT LOOKS LIKE DOUG
AND CHERIEN'S MONTHLY EXPENSES
ARE ABOUT $7,500 A MONTH.

15:42.944 --> 15:47.081
WE GOTTA FIND ABOUT EIGHT GRAND
A MONTH FOR THIS NEW LIFE.

15:47.114 --> 15:49.617
AND BY "WE," I MEAN YOU.
THANK YOU.

15:49.651 --> 15:53.621
WELL, I MEAN, YEAH,
IF WE DON'T WANT THE CREDIT
COLLECTORS ON OUR ASSES.

15:53.655 --> 15:56.591
JUDGING FROM HIS TAX RETURNS,
DOUG WAS RAKING IN THE KOOSH.

15:56.624 --> 15:59.861
‐ DOUG HAD TO BE PLANNING ON
MAKING A LIVING HERE.
‐ FUNNY YOU SHOULD MENTI
ON THAT,

15:59.894 --> 16:03.998
BECAUSE DOUGIE WAS LOOKING
FOR WORK... AS A LAWYER,

16:04.031 --> 16:06.367
AND YOU'VE GOT
A LUNCH INTERVIEW TODAY.

16:06.400 --> 16:08.335
YEAH? LET ME
HAVE A LOOK AT THAT.

16:45.740 --> 16:48.510
[ Deep Voice ]
HI. DOUG RICH.

16:48.543 --> 16:50.578
[ High‐pitched Voice ]
YEAH. UH, UH, DOUG RICH.

16:50.612 --> 16:52.580
HEY. HOW YOU DOING?
DOUG RICH.

16:52.614 --> 16:54.582
HI, I'M DOUG.
I'M DOUG.

16:54.616 --> 16:56.918
[ Deep Voice ]
I'M DOUG.
HI. DOUG.

16:56.951 --> 16:59.220
DOUG RICH.
[ High‐pitched Voice ]
DOUG RICH.

17:08.128 --> 17:10.097
YOU LIKE THAT?
MM‐HMM.

17:10.131 --> 17:12.133
IT'S PRETTY, HUH?

17:13.867 --> 17:15.837
‐ HELLO.
‐ [ Cael Laughs ]

17:15.869 --> 17:19.173
DI DI.
[ Laughs ]

17:19.205 --> 17:21.342
[ Cael ]
YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD, DAD.
YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD.

17:21.375 --> 17:24.912
OH, LORD.
YOU ARE REALLY
GONNA DO THIS?

17:24.945 --> 17:27.749
IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M GONNA GET THE JOB.

17:27.781 --> 17:29.851
JUST GOTTA TURN UP.
DOUG DOESN'T TURN UP,

17:29.884 --> 17:33.521
SOMEONE'S GONNA WONDER WHY,
AND WE DON'T WANT THAT, DO WE?

17:33.555 --> 17:36.190
‐ WHY DON'T YOU JUST
CALL IN SICK?
‐ TOO LATE.

17:36.223 --> 17:39.026
WOULDN'T LOOK RIGHT.
YOU DON'T KNOW THE FIRST
THING ABOUT THE LAW.

17:39.060 --> 17:42.096
OH, YEAH?
WELL, I TALKED MY WAY
OUT OF THAT NASHVILLE THING.

17:42.129 --> 17:45.032
‐ THE JUDGE WAS DRUNK.
‐ BULLSHIT IS BULLSHIT.

17:45.066 --> 17:47.034
OH, I KNOW BULLSHIT, WAYNE.

17:47.068 --> 17:50.104
AND RIGHT NOW,
YOU ARE FULL OF IT.

17:50.137 --> 17:52.039
YOU JUST WANT TO PLAY.

17:52.073 --> 17:54.576
YOU JUST WANT TO SEE
IF YOU CAN GET THIS JOB.

17:57.244 --> 17:59.380
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
LET ME DO MY THING?

17:59.413 --> 18:02.216
YOU JUST SIT THERE
AND LOOK PRETTY.

18:02.249 --> 18:04.886
DON'T BREAK ANY LAWS.
DON'T BREAK ANY WINDOWS.

18:04.919 --> 18:06.921
DON'T BREAK ANYTHING.

18:07.922 --> 18:10.457
COME ON, CAEL.

18:10.491 --> 18:13.595
YOU SON OF A BITCH!

18:14.796 --> 18:16.430
YOU, GET OUT!

18:16.463 --> 18:18.499
GO ON!

18:18.533 --> 18:20.802
JUST LIKE YOUR DAD.
DON'T YOU SMILE AT ME!

18:23.437 --> 18:25.039
ASSHOLE.
[ Door Closes ]

18:27.609 --> 18:31.212
"BREAK ANYTHING."
BREAK YOUR ASS.

18:32.279 --> 18:34.281
ONE PILL.

18:38.653 --> 18:40.655
WELL, THAT AIN'T GONNA DO IT.

18:45.459 --> 18:47.695
GODDAMN IT, DI DI!
DAMN IT!

18:58.039 --> 19:00.141
PUT THE COOKIE DOWN.

19:00.174 --> 19:02.844
PUT IT DOWN, HALF‐PINT.
PUT THE COOKIE DOWN!

19:02.877 --> 19:06.213
BUT I WANT ONE.
PUT THE COOKIE DOWN. YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE TO MAKE YOUR OWN.

19:16.591 --> 19:18.826
[ Beeps ]

19:23.064 --> 19:25.066
[ Beeping ]

19:39.180 --> 19:41.348
[ Door Closes ]

19:41.382 --> 19:44.318
HI, NINA.
I MADE YOU SOME COOKIES.

19:44.351 --> 19:46.387
GIVE ME SOME DRUGS?

19:46.420 --> 19:49.256
HI, NINA.
I MADE YOU SOME COOKIES.

19:49.290 --> 19:51.859
YOU GOT ANY MORE
OF THEM LITTLE PILLS?

19:53.027 --> 19:55.697
HI, NINA.
GOT ANY DRUGS?

19:57.398 --> 19:59.567
SHIT, SHIT, SHIT.

19:59.601 --> 20:01.669
[ Doorbell Rings ]

20:01.703 --> 20:04.338
WELL, HI THERE, DAHLIA.
HI, NINA.

20:04.371 --> 20:06.608
I MADE YOU
SOME COOKIES.

20:07.709 --> 20:10.211
THANK YOU FOR MY HAND
AND EVERYTHING.

20:11.245 --> 20:14.048
[ Chuckles ]
WELL, THANKS, HON.

20:17.084 --> 20:19.353
SO YOU WANT TO COME IN.

20:19.386 --> 20:21.388
OH, YEAH.

20:25.392 --> 20:27.695
I SAW YOUR TWO GIRLS OUT
RIDIN' THEIR BIKES TODAY.

20:27.729 --> 20:30.231
MY GIRLS?
UH,

20:30.264 --> 20:33.100
DI DI AND THE‐‐
AND THE LITTLE ONE.

20:34.168 --> 20:36.170
OH, SAM.

20:37.438 --> 20:39.440
YEAH.

20:41.008 --> 20:43.945
SHE'S CUTE.
REAL CUTE.

20:43.978 --> 20:45.947
YEAH, SHE IS.

20:45.980 --> 20:48.482
REAL CUTE.

20:48.516 --> 20:51.385
WHAT SCHOOL
YOU GOT 'EM IN?

20:51.418 --> 20:54.488
OH‐‐ OH,
WE HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

20:56.123 --> 20:59.561
SO, NINA.
MMM?

20:59.594 --> 21:02.263
OH, NINA,

21:02.296 --> 21:04.566
YOU KNOW THOSE LITTLE PILLS
YOU GAVE ME YESTERDAY?

21:04.599 --> 21:07.001
I WAS JUST WONDERIN', LIKE,

21:07.034 --> 21:10.071
IF YOU JUST HAD, LIKE,
A FEW MORE.

21:10.104 --> 21:12.339
GAVE YOU FIVE, HON.

21:12.373 --> 21:14.642
THAT'S ENOUGH TO LAST YOU
FOUR MORE DAYS.

21:15.710 --> 21:17.745
I KNOW, BUT...

21:17.779 --> 21:20.582
WOULD YOU BELIEVE I DROPPED
THEM ALL IN THE TOILET?

21:20.615 --> 21:23.518
[ Laughs ]
DARLIN', MAYBE YOU
NEED TO ASK YOURSELF...

21:23.551 --> 21:25.687
WHY YOU NEED 'EM
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

21:31.392 --> 21:33.761
[ Laughing ]

21:33.795 --> 21:36.430
ON SECOND THOUGHT,
IT'S REALLY
NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

21:36.463 --> 21:41.769
BUT WHAT‐‐ WHAT I CAN DO
IS GIVE YOU THE NAME OF
A NICE DOCTOR IN TOWN.

21:41.803 --> 21:43.805
[ Clears Throat ]

21:45.339 --> 21:47.341
DR. SALHANNY?

21:48.710 --> 21:52.346
HE'S A SENSITIVE MAN
WHO UNDERSTANDS
THE SOMETIMES...

21:52.379 --> 21:55.349
DISTRESSING NATURE
OF MODERN LIFE.

21:55.382 --> 21:57.384
MM‐HMM.

22:00.655 --> 22:04.058
HOW LONG WILL YOU BE NEEDING
A RENTAL CAR, MR. PRATT?

22:04.091 --> 22:07.161
A COUPLE OF WEEKS.
MY 740 IS IN THE SHOP.

22:07.194 --> 22:09.831
CHIP HERE TOOK IT OUT
FOR A DRIVE,
GOT IT SIDESWIPED.

22:09.864 --> 22:12.667
‐ IT WAS SOME DICKWAD
IN A CORVETTE, CHUCK.
‐ DUDE.

22:12.700 --> 22:15.537
‐ SO CHIP WON'T BE
DRIVING FOR A WHILE.
‐ WELL, CHUCK,

22:15.570 --> 22:17.238
IT WASN'T EXACTLY MY FAULT,
WAS IT?

22:17.271 --> 22:20.007
TROY, COULD YOU TELL CHIP
TO TELL THAT TO ALLSTATE?

22:23.177 --> 22:26.347
WELL, GEEZ, UH, IF YOU'RE
USED TO DRIVING A 740,

22:26.380 --> 22:29.917
YOU'LL PROBABLY BE INTERESTED
IN RENTING A CAR FROM
OUR PRESTIGE COLLECTION.

22:29.951 --> 22:32.053
JAGUAR, ROVER,

22:33.054 --> 22:35.056
MERCEDES.

22:38.593 --> 22:41.963
[ Woman ] SURE. WE CAN‐‐
WE CAN PICK YOU UP.
YES, WE WOULD.

22:46.768 --> 22:49.737
COME ON, MOM!
I'M COMIN'.

22:49.771 --> 22:51.773
YOU'RE SO SLOW.

22:51.806 --> 22:54.375
[ Di Di ]
SOMEBODY'S TIRED.
[ Sam ] HURRY UP.

22:55.543 --> 22:57.845
[ Groans ]

22:57.879 --> 23:01.749
COME ON.
I'M GONNA SNAG MY PANTY HOSE
ON THIS BIKE CHAIN.

23:02.383 --> 23:04.385
WHO THE HELL WEARS PANTY HOSE?

23:05.820 --> 23:09.223
STUCK IN BUFFERVILLE,
CIRCA 1954.

23:09.256 --> 23:11.526
OH, MAN.
[ Sam ]
COME ON!

23:11.559 --> 23:14.128
WAIT UP!

23:14.161 --> 23:16.631
‐ DI DI. THIS SUCKS!
‐ [ Both ]
HEY!

23:16.664 --> 23:18.465
[ Di Di ]
STOP!

23:18.499 --> 23:20.301
HEY!
HEY!

23:20.334 --> 23:22.303
[ Di Di ]
STOP!
[ Sam ] STOP!

23:22.336 --> 23:24.371
[ Di Di ]
THE R. V.! STOP IT!

23:24.405 --> 23:27.374
[ Dahlia ]
AW, SHIT. I KNEW WE SHOULDN'T
HAVE PARKED THERE.

23:27.408 --> 23:30.778
THAT'S RIGHT.
Y'ALL ARE TRESPASSIN'.
HI THERE.

23:30.812 --> 23:33.380
YOU'RE ON MY LANDS.
I'M TELLING MY HUSBAND
WE NEED A FENCE.

23:33.414 --> 23:35.983
SO, WHAT,
YOU JUST HAD IT TOWED?

23:36.017 --> 23:38.720
HOW'D Y'ALL GET IN
THE FRONT GATE?

23:38.753 --> 23:40.722
WE LIVE HERE.
YEAH, IN THAT...

23:40.755 --> 23:42.724
REALLY BIG HOUSE
JUST RIGHT OVER THERE.

23:42.757 --> 23:44.559
I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU BEFORE.

23:44.592 --> 23:48.229
[ Scoffs ]
SO YOU KNOW EVERYONE THEN?

23:48.262 --> 23:49.764
WELL, AS A MATTER
OF FACT, I DO.

23:49.797 --> 23:53.635
I'M HARTLEY UNDERWOOD,
PRESIDENT OF EHA, THE EDENFALLS
HOMEOWNERS ASSOCIATION.

23:53.668 --> 23:55.069
GREAT.

23:55.102 --> 23:58.305
AND WHO ARE YOU?

23:58.339 --> 24:00.675
I'M CHERIEN RICH.
THIS IS DI DI. THIS IS SAM.

24:00.708 --> 24:02.744
MY HUSBAND'S DOUG RICH.

24:02.777 --> 24:04.411
HE'S A SECURITIES LAWYER.

24:04.445 --> 24:07.314
‐ HE'S A REPUBLICAN.
‐ THE RICHES?

24:07.348 --> 24:09.416
I WAS TOLD THERE
WOULDN'T BE CHILDREN.
YEAH.

24:09.450 --> 24:12.787
CONDOMS AIN'T WHAT
THEY USED TO BE.
HUH.

24:12.820 --> 24:16.290
WELL, IT WAS REAL NICE
TO MEET YOU, "SHARLENE."

24:16.323 --> 24:21.863
OH, AND BY THE WAY, WE ARE
NOT ZONED FOR BOAT OR R.V.
PARKIN' HERE IN EDENFALLS.

24:21.896 --> 24:24.231
GUESS YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
MAKE OTHER ARRANGEMENTS.

24:26.333 --> 24:29.003
IT'S CHERIEN,
YOU STUPID LUDNEY BITCH.

24:30.137 --> 24:32.139
WHAT ABOUT
MY COLORED PENCILS?

24:32.173 --> 24:34.441
HEY. HEY, WE'RE GONNA GET
'EM BACK, ALL RIGHT, HONEY?

24:34.475 --> 24:36.778
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
I PROMISE.
OH, MY GOD.

24:36.811 --> 24:38.813
OH, MY GOD!

24:38.846 --> 24:41.482
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH HER NOW?

24:49.323 --> 24:52.159
[ Sam ]
COME ON, MOM.
OKAY.

24:52.193 --> 24:55.029
EIGHT FROM THE DOOR,
WHICH WOULD BE HERE.

24:55.062 --> 24:58.299
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR,

24:58.332 --> 25:01.669
FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

25:05.206 --> 25:07.509
OH. W‐‐

25:07.542 --> 25:10.077
WHICH TREE WAS IT?

25:10.111 --> 25:12.246
OH, GOD.

25:12.279 --> 25:14.281
OH, MAN.

25:16.417 --> 25:18.419
‐ HEY. MOM.
‐ YEAH?

25:18.452 --> 25:20.688
‐ WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
‐ NOTHIN'.

25:27.762 --> 25:30.765
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR,

25:30.798 --> 25:34.035
FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

25:35.537 --> 25:38.172
OKAY. LET'S GO.

25:38.205 --> 25:40.241
[ Dahlia ]
$235?

25:40.274 --> 25:43.878
[ Man Exhales ]
175 FOR THE TOWING,

25:43.911 --> 25:47.615
PLUS $60 FOR THE TICKET.
WELL, ALL RIGHT.

25:47.649 --> 25:50.117
THIS HAS JUST BEEN
A BIG OLD STUPID MISTAKE.

25:50.151 --> 25:55.022
PLUS I'M GONNA NEED TO SEE
A VALID DRIVER'S LICENSE
AND PROOF OF OWNERSHIP.

25:55.056 --> 25:56.257
PROOF OF OWNERSHIP?

25:56.290 --> 25:57.959
UH‐‐

25:57.992 --> 26:00.528
WELL, WE JUST MOVED HERE,

26:00.562 --> 26:02.964
SO I DON'T KNOW WHERE
MY HUSBAND KEEPS
ALL THE DOCUMENTS.

26:02.997 --> 26:06.167
SO, IF YOU'LL JUST‐‐
IT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

26:07.602 --> 26:09.737
FOR ALL I KNOW,
YOU COULD HAVE STOLE IT.

26:31.526 --> 26:34.729
MAY SHIT RAIN DOWN
ON THESE HONEST BUFFER WAYS.

26:34.762 --> 26:37.865
‐ YEAH. I TOLD YOU.
‐ WE GOTTA GO WITH
A DIFFERENT PLAN.

26:40.835 --> 26:43.437
YOU GAME?

26:43.470 --> 26:45.840
[ Sighs ]
SURE.

26:47.775 --> 26:50.111
LET'S GET SAM HIS
COLORED PENCILS BACK.
HEY. WAIT UP.

26:50.144 --> 26:52.146
HOLD ON.

26:54.115 --> 26:57.819
I KNOW YOUR BOY DALE
HAS BEEN A GREAT
DISAPPOINTMENT TO YOU, EARL.

26:57.852 --> 27:00.321
WELL, HE'S DISAPPOINTED
ME TOO.

27:00.354 --> 27:02.524
EARL. EARL!

27:02.557 --> 27:04.892
MMM? MMM?
HI.

27:06.861 --> 27:08.830
TEA?

27:08.863 --> 27:12.299
NOW, US DANNEGANS‐‐ WE'VE
BEEN WANTIN' A RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOU MALLOYS...

27:12.333 --> 27:14.368
EVER SINCE THAT DI DI
WAS A YOUNG UN.

27:14.401 --> 27:17.872
I EVEN OFFERED WAYNE
$50,000 TO TAKE KEN ON,

27:17.905 --> 27:21.442
BUT IT JUST DON'T LOOK LIKE
THAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

27:21.475 --> 27:24.345
DALE JUST AIN'T STRONG
ENOUGH TO BE THE BOSS.

27:24.378 --> 27:27.882
I MEAN, HE ISN'T.
YOU KNOW THAT. AND WHAT
I'VE BEEN NOTICIN'...

27:27.915 --> 27:30.151
IS THAT A LOT OF
FOLK AROUND HERE‐‐

27:30.184 --> 27:33.387
WELL, THEY RESPECT KEN
A WHOLE LOT.

27:33.420 --> 27:36.223
SO, WITH YOUR BLESSING, I‐‐
[ Door Opens ]

27:36.257 --> 27:38.492
HI, GINNY‐GIN.

27:38.526 --> 27:41.863
NICE OF YOU
TO VISIT DADDY, BUT HE'S
A LITTLE TIRED RIGHT NOW.

27:41.896 --> 27:45.633
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME.
NO ONE TALKS TO DADDY
UNLESS I SAY.

27:45.667 --> 27:49.303
NO ONE.
GET THE HELL AWAY FROM ME.
I'M DONE WITH YOU.

27:49.336 --> 27:52.674
I WOULDN'T GO TALKIN' UP
THAT DUMB‐ASS BROTHER OF YOURS.

27:53.675 --> 27:56.010
SOMETHIN' BAD
MIGHT HAPPEN TO HIM...

27:56.043 --> 27:58.012
AND YOU.

27:58.045 --> 28:01.816
REAL BAD.
AND NO ONE WILL GIVE A SHIT.

28:01.849 --> 28:05.452
DON'T MESS WITH ME.
I KNOW THINGS.

28:08.255 --> 28:11.258
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

28:20.201 --> 28:23.605
HOW DO PEOPLE GO ABOUT
THEIR DAY IN SHOES LIKE THESE?

28:23.638 --> 28:26.040
HMM?

28:29.043 --> 28:31.012
[ Grunts ]
OW. SH‐‐

28:31.045 --> 28:34.348
I GOT THINGS TO DO.
I CAN'T DO SHIT IN THESE SHOES.
SHH!

28:34.381 --> 28:37.284
TAKE MY PURSE.
YOU CAN'T KEEP IT.

28:40.922 --> 28:42.957
I LIKE THE SHOES.
YOU CAN KEEP 'EM.

28:42.990 --> 28:45.760
REALLY?
COME ON.

28:45.793 --> 28:47.862
HOLD ON. HOLD ON. HOLD ON.

28:47.895 --> 28:51.666
[ Sighs ]
YOU KNOW, I‐I WASN'T EVEN
PARKED THERE THAT LONG.

28:53.901 --> 28:55.903
[ Man ]
OH, SO YOU THINK
IT WAS TOWED, HUH?

28:55.937 --> 28:58.873
[ Di Di ]
YEAH. YEAH. TOWED. I GUESS
THAT'S PROBABLY WHY I'M HERE.

28:58.906 --> 29:01.976
[ Chuckles, Sighs ]

29:02.009 --> 29:05.780
YOU KNOW, I HAD THIS, UH‐‐
THIS SCALE MODEL
OF ANCIENT ROME IN MY TRUNK,

29:05.813 --> 29:08.916
AND IF I‐‐ IF I DON'T FIND IT,
I AM REALLY SO DEAD.

29:08.950 --> 29:12.954
I‐‐ IT'S REALLY MY LAST CHANCE
TO GET A "C."

29:12.987 --> 29:16.724
I MADE THESE LITTLE EMPERORS
AND GLADIATORS AND...

29:16.758 --> 29:20.127
VESTAL VIRGINS AND STUFF.

29:20.161 --> 29:22.163
I MEAN, I REALLY
WORKED MY ASS OFF.

29:23.330 --> 29:25.499
WH‐WHAT KIND OF CAR
WAS IT AGAIN, HON?

29:25.533 --> 29:27.569
UM,

29:27.602 --> 29:29.904
A BROWN COROLLA.

29:29.937 --> 29:32.807
YOU THINK Y'ALL COULD HELP?
WELL, SURE.

29:32.840 --> 29:36.143
[ Man ]
LET'S GO LOOK FOR IT.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

29:36.177 --> 29:39.781
OH. OH, MY GOD.
THAT'S IT. THAT'S‐‐ THAT'S
MY CAR RIGHT THERE. THAT ONE.

29:39.814 --> 29:42.349
UH, I'M PRETTY SURE
THAT'S NOT IT, HON.
UH, THAT'S A MALIBU.

29:42.383 --> 29:46.654
OH. WOW. THEY LOOK
EXTREMELY SIMILAR. YEAH.

29:46.688 --> 29:48.990
WELL, THAT'S A MALIBU.
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

29:49.023 --> 29:51.425
[ Engine Starts ]
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST KEEP LOOKIN' THEN?

29:51.458 --> 29:53.494
WELL, YEAH.
OKAY.

29:53.528 --> 29:56.598
‐ HEY! HEY! WHAT THE HELL!
‐ HEE‐HEE!

29:56.631 --> 30:00.467
HEY, STOP!
STOP, YOU! HEY!

30:00.501 --> 30:02.504
WHOO!

30:03.971 --> 30:05.973
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?
DO IT, MOM!

30:06.007 --> 30:09.243
‐ YOU GOT IT.
‐ STOP! STOP RIGHT THERE!

30:11.879 --> 30:13.881
HEY!

30:15.149 --> 30:17.785
[ Tires Squeal ]

30:17.819 --> 30:19.721
[ Man ]
THAT GIRL.

30:19.754 --> 30:23.190
MOM, WHY DID WE PARK HERE?

30:23.224 --> 30:26.160
IT'S A FREE COUNTRY, AIN'T IT?
YOU HEARD HER.
WE'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO.

30:26.193 --> 30:28.195
OH, ASK ME IF I CARE.

30:32.767 --> 30:35.002
YOU KNOW,

30:35.036 --> 30:39.741
ROY LIDGE COULD NOT
FIND A SINGLE GOOD WORD
TO SAY ABOUT YOU, DOUG.

30:41.709 --> 30:46.413
WELL, ROY LIDGE COULD NOT
FIND A SINGLE GOOD WORD
TO SAY ABOUT GANDHI.

30:46.447 --> 30:48.415
ACTUALLY,

30:48.449 --> 30:51.886
HE WENT COMPLETELY NUTS
WHEN HE HEARD
YOU WERE COMIN' IN.

30:51.919 --> 30:55.389
AH, WELL, THAT'S ROY.
WHAT A NUT.

30:55.422 --> 30:57.525
I UNDERSTAND LIDGE
IS AN ANIMAL.

30:57.559 --> 31:01.095
YEAH, HE IS.
EVERY DAY WE'D RATTLE HIS CAGE,
TOSS HIM A STEAK.

31:03.765 --> 31:05.967
WHY ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN HAYDEN‐JAVITZ, DOUG?

31:09.370 --> 31:12.507
WELL, I KNOW YOU'RE A BUNCH
OF TOUGH SONS OF BITCHES...

31:12.540 --> 31:16.578
WHO DON'T STOP UNTIL
YOU BRING AN OPPONENT
TO THEIR KNEES.

31:16.611 --> 31:21.015
BUT I ALSO KNOW YOU WON
THE CLIENT CHOICE AWARD,
WHICH MEANS THAT‐‐

31:21.048 --> 31:26.521
THIS MEANS NO MATTER HOW
HARD YOU SCREW 'EM, THEY STILL
LOVE YOU IN THE MORNING.

31:26.554 --> 31:28.590
AND I WANT IN ON THAT.

31:28.623 --> 31:32.193
LOT OF LAWYERS DO, DOUG.
WHAT MAKES YOU RIGHT FOR US?

31:32.226 --> 31:35.462
NAPOLÉON USED TO SAY,
"I KNOW HE'S A BRILLIANT
GENERAL, BUT IS HE LUCKY?"

31:35.496 --> 31:37.464
HE USED TO SAY IT IN FRENCH.

31:37.498 --> 31:39.801
BUT I'M THE LUCKY GUY.

31:39.834 --> 31:41.636
JE SUIS LUCKY.

31:41.669 --> 31:45.573
I'M LIKE A RACEHORSE.
THAT'S BETTER.
LIKE, UH, SEABISCUIT.

31:45.607 --> 31:50.211
THE SEABISCUIT OF
THE NON‐SEABISCUIT WORLD.
YOU KNOW?

31:50.244 --> 31:52.379
I JUST WORK VERY HARD.
AT KERRIMAN FOX,

31:52.413 --> 31:56.317
I BILLED MORE HOURS IN A MONTH
THAN MOST GUYS DO IN‐IN A YEAR‐‐
IN 10 YEARS.

31:56.350 --> 31:59.554
WELL, A YEAR IS MORE REALISTIC.
I JUST WORK LIKE AN IDIOT.

31:59.587 --> 32:02.590
I JUST DON'T HAVE ANY LIFE
OUTSIDE THE FIRM. THAT'S ALL.

32:02.624 --> 32:06.060
I'M LIKE AN ANIMAL.
LIKE A NOCTURNAL ANIMAL.
LIKE AN OWL.

32:06.093 --> 32:08.329
OR LIKE A‐‐ UH, ONE OF
THOSE, YOU KNOW, THING‐‐

32:08.362 --> 32:12.900
I'M LIKE A TIGER.
A SABER‐TOOTH TIGER,
AT NIGHT.

32:12.934 --> 32:16.270
YOU KNOW?
A BIG, NIGHTTIME TIGER.
THAT'S ME.

32:16.303 --> 32:18.439
YOU KNOW?

32:22.944 --> 32:26.581
BUT, BOB, I DIDN'T COME
TO LOUISIANA FOR THE ÉTOUFFÉE.

32:26.614 --> 32:29.984
WELL, WELL, WELL.
THE TIGHTEST ASSHOLES
IN THE CLUB.

32:30.017 --> 32:32.954
[ Clears Throat ]
I SURE AS HELL HOPE YOU DIDN'T
COME HERE FOR THESE BUBBAS.

32:32.987 --> 32:35.590
[ Laughs ]
HOW YOU DOIN', DOUG?

32:35.623 --> 32:37.859
GOOD TO SEE YOU. BOB.

32:38.960 --> 32:42.296
♪♪♪ [ Humming ]
HEY, TOMMY!

32:42.329 --> 32:45.266
HOW YOU HITTIN' 'EM?
[ Tommy ]
HI THERE, HUGH.

32:45.299 --> 32:47.001
YOU KNOW PANETTA?

32:47.034 --> 32:49.003
NO.

32:49.036 --> 32:52.607
OH, YEAH. YEAH.
WELL, JUST ENOUGH TO KICK
HIS ASS ON THE GOLF COURSE.

32:52.640 --> 32:54.441
[ Laughs ]
GOOD.

32:54.475 --> 32:58.145
PANETTA'S A SCUMBAG.
BIGGEST THIEF IN
THE REAL ESTATE BIZ.

32:58.179 --> 33:02.083
CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MANY LAWSUITS
WE'VE FILED AGAINST THAT PRICK.

33:03.317 --> 33:06.353
YEAH? HOW MANY YOU WON?

33:11.392 --> 33:13.728
SEE, THE THING ABOUT
GUYS LIKE PANETTA...

33:13.761 --> 33:17.665
IS HE'S GOT WEAKNESSES
WHICH CAN BE FOUND IF YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

33:19.701 --> 33:22.003
YOU'VE GOTTA BEAT HIM
AT HIS OWN GAME.

33:23.404 --> 33:25.339
I ALREADY HAVE.

33:34.782 --> 33:36.784
[ Doorbell Rings ]

33:45.059 --> 33:48.195
HI, DI DI.
IS YOUR MAMA HOME,
'CAUSE I'D LI‐‐

33:48.229 --> 33:50.898
HEY, MOM.

33:57.271 --> 34:00.708
‐ WELL, HI, MISS HARTLEY.
‐ WHO THE HELL
DO YOU THINK YOU ARE?

34:00.742 --> 34:04.779
EXCUSE ME?
I TOLD YOU NOT TO PARK
THAT SHIT HEAP ON MY LANDS.

34:04.812 --> 34:06.781
‐ WELL, I DIDN'T.
‐ HUH.

34:06.814 --> 34:09.583
WELL, THESE TWO TIRES ARE
NINE INCHES ON MY PROPERTY.

34:11.886 --> 34:14.021
OH, HONEY.
YOU WOULDN'T KNOW NINE INCHES...

34:14.054 --> 34:16.456
IF IT JUMPED IN YOUR BED
AND SMACKED YOU UPSIDE THE HEAD.

34:16.489 --> 34:19.126
OH, DON'T YOU
TALK TRASH TO ME.

34:19.159 --> 34:21.696
I WILL HAVE THAT THING TOWED
TO THE JUNKYARD THIS TIME.

34:21.728 --> 34:25.900
YOU TOUCH MY R. V.,
I WILL KILL YOU.

34:25.933 --> 34:28.536
REALLY? WELL, MAYBE
I SHOULD CALL THE
POLICE RIGHT NOW.

34:28.570 --> 34:30.705
‐ WELL, UH‐‐
‐ WELL, YOU CAN CALL GODDAMN
JESUS CHRIST‐‐

34:30.737 --> 34:33.875
OH, DON'T YOU TAKE
THE LORD'S NAME
IN VAIN WITH M‐‐

34:33.908 --> 34:35.976
DON'T YOU MESS WITH ME,
YOU STUCK‐UP LITTLE BITCH!

34:36.010 --> 34:38.079
IT WILL NOT END PRETTY.

34:38.112 --> 34:40.481
OH!

34:48.590 --> 34:50.592
YOU ONLY GOT ONE ARM!

34:52.025 --> 34:54.228
YOU'RE CRAZY.

34:54.261 --> 34:57.665
YOU JUST MADE A BIG MISTAKE,
SHARLENE.

35:04.939 --> 35:06.941
THANK YOU.

35:09.644 --> 35:11.679
YOU JUST BEAT UP
A ONE‐ARMED WOMAN.

35:11.713 --> 35:13.748
WELL, HOW WAS I
SUPPOSED TO KNOW?

35:13.781 --> 35:15.917
I AIN'T NEVER‐‐

35:15.950 --> 35:18.553
I AIN'T NEVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE THAT BEFORE.

35:20.054 --> 35:22.757
"THE ISSUER OF ANY SECURITY...

35:22.790 --> 35:25.593
"UPON WHICH A RESTRICTION
OR TRANSFER HAS BEEN IMPOSED,

35:25.627 --> 35:28.763
"PURSUANT TO
SECTION 260.102.34,

35:28.796 --> 35:32.433
"SHALL CAUSE A COPY
OF THIS SECTION...

35:32.466 --> 35:35.102
TO BE DELIVERED
TO EACH 'ISSUEE.'"

35:35.136 --> 35:37.271
HAVE YOU ANY IDEA
WHAT THAT SHIT MEANS?

35:37.304 --> 35:39.541
NO, SIR.
I'M SORRY. I HAVE NO IDEA.

35:39.574 --> 35:41.976
BOBBY, BOB, BOBBY,
JUST CALL ME WAYNE.

35:42.009 --> 35:44.045
OR CALL ME DOUG.

35:44.078 --> 35:46.113
WAYNE'S MY MIDDLE NAME.

35:46.147 --> 35:49.050
‐ OKAY. DOUG.
‐ YEAH. RIGHT.

35:50.818 --> 35:52.820
WHO AM I KIDDIN'?

35:52.854 --> 35:54.989
OH, NO. THIS WON'T DO.

35:55.022 --> 35:57.792
MAN SHOULD NEVER DRINK ALONE.
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR FRIENDS?

35:57.825 --> 36:01.796
WELL, YOU KNOW, HUGH.
PLACES TO GO, PEOPLE TO SUE.
[ Chuckles ]

36:01.829 --> 36:05.466
OH, I COULD HAVE
USED YOU OUT THERE
ON THAT COURSE TODAY, DOUG.

36:05.499 --> 36:07.802
GOT MY ASS KICKED.

36:07.835 --> 36:09.871
HAPPENS TO
THE BEST OF US, HUGH.

36:09.904 --> 36:12.740
YOU'RE NOT PAYIN'
FOR THIS SHIT, ARE YA?
I HAVEN'T YET.

36:14.008 --> 36:15.977
JUST PUT IT ON MY TAB, BOBBY.
COME ON.

36:16.010 --> 36:17.912
LET ME BUY YOU A REAL DRINK.

36:18.913 --> 36:21.215
COME ON.
HIS TAB.

36:21.248 --> 36:23.250
[ Birds Chirping ]

36:30.525 --> 36:32.527
♪♪♪ [ Headphones: Rock ]

36:33.928 --> 36:35.930
HEY.

36:51.278 --> 36:53.280
[ Exhales ]

36:53.314 --> 36:55.349
MOM'S CRAZY.

36:55.382 --> 36:57.384
YEAH.

37:05.426 --> 37:07.795
I GUESS WE'RE
STAYING HERE, HUH?

37:08.996 --> 37:10.998
I GUESS SO.

37:13.768 --> 37:15.970
[ Sighs ]

37:21.976 --> 37:24.045
POOL'S COOL.

37:24.078 --> 37:26.648
YEAH.

37:34.488 --> 37:36.758
I GUESS YOU'RE GONNA BE
SLEEPING IN THE HOUSE NOW.

37:42.096 --> 37:43.931
WE NEVER HAD A POOL BEFORE.

37:55.176 --> 37:59.246
[ Chuckling ]
OH! OH! OH! YEAH, HUH?

37:59.280 --> 38:01.282
[ Gunshots ]

38:05.119 --> 38:07.622
LIMBAUGH,
YOU FREAKIN' DRUG ADDICT!

38:11.492 --> 38:13.528
[ Grumbles ]
I TRIED EVERYTHING.

38:14.729 --> 38:17.098
[ Grumbles ]
VITAMINS.

38:17.131 --> 38:19.100
I TRIED LIPITOR.

38:19.133 --> 38:22.504
TRIED AROMATHERAPY.
TRIED JUMPIN' OFF A CLIFF.

38:22.537 --> 38:27.308
TRIED STRAPPIN'
ELECTRIC WIRES TO MY NADS.
NOTHIN' WORKED.

38:27.341 --> 38:29.443
MY NUMBERS WERE JUST‐‐
BLOOD PRESSURE NUMBERS‐‐

38:29.476 --> 38:31.513
SHIT. FLYIN' OFF THE CHARTS.

38:31.546 --> 38:34.015
THE ONLY THING THAT WORKS...

38:35.416 --> 38:36.618
IS RIGHT HERE.

38:36.651 --> 38:39.220
ISN'T THAT JIM,
MY NEIGHBOR?

38:39.253 --> 38:41.222
[ Clears Throat ]
SURE IS.

38:41.255 --> 38:45.126
NEIGHBORS, FRIENDS,
EMPLOYEES, PEOPLE I KNOW.

38:45.159 --> 38:47.494
SHIT. SOME OF 'EM
ARE EVEN PEOPLE I LIKE.

38:47.529 --> 38:49.496
SEE THIS?

38:50.932 --> 38:53.234
IT'S MODELED ON
HERMANN GÖRING'S
SUMMER PLACE.

38:54.669 --> 38:57.972
YEAH. I NOTICED YOU HAVE
THE SAME PATIO FURNITURE.
YEAH.

38:58.005 --> 39:01.042
YOU SHOULD SEE THE BUNKER.
[ Laughs ]

39:01.075 --> 39:03.344
HEY, DOUG.
HUGH.

39:03.377 --> 39:05.346
WANT TO TRY THE NEXT ONE?

39:05.379 --> 39:08.115
SURE.

39:14.856 --> 39:16.858
[ Gunshot ]

39:23.364 --> 39:25.399
NOT BAD.

39:25.432 --> 39:27.368
NICE GROUPIN'.

39:28.570 --> 39:32.574
[ Laughs ]
YOU'RE A SHOOTER,
AREN'T YOU, DOUG?

39:32.607 --> 39:35.777
SHOT A FEW
IN MY TIME, HUGH.
MM‐HMM.

39:35.810 --> 39:37.879
A FEW WHAT?
[ Clears Throat ]

39:37.912 --> 39:41.382
A FEW TRESPASSERS,
HOSTILE WITNESSES.

39:42.884 --> 39:45.653
SO WHAT WERE YOU DOIN' WITH
THOSE HAYDEN‐JAVITZ PRICKS?

39:46.888 --> 39:49.456
JUST LISTENING TO WHAT
THEY HAD TO SAY, HUGH.

39:51.058 --> 39:52.994
[ Target Whirs ]

39:53.728 --> 39:55.229
[ Gunshots ]

39:57.264 --> 39:59.801
MISS SCHLEEWEE,
FOURTH GRADE.

40:01.503 --> 40:05.039
I LOVED HER. YOU ASK ME,
I WOULDN'T WORK AT
ANY ONE OF THOSE JOINTS.

40:05.072 --> 40:07.041
[ Clears Throat ]
TOO MANY ASSHOLES.

40:07.074 --> 40:09.210
OBSERVING YOU,
WATCHING YOU.

40:09.243 --> 40:11.746
CAN'T EVEN TAKE A DUMP
WITHOUT EVERYONE
KNOWIN' ABOUT IT.

40:11.779 --> 40:15.249
THEY'VE ALL TRIED
TO GET A PIECE OF ME
AT ONE POINT OR ANOTHER.

40:15.282 --> 40:17.952
I SHOVED THOSE LAWSUITS
RIGHT BACK UP THEIR ASSES.

40:17.985 --> 40:20.454
CAN'T TOUCH THIS.

40:20.487 --> 40:22.890
THEY'RE AMATEURS.

40:22.924 --> 40:24.926
EVER DONE IN‐HOUSE?

40:26.360 --> 40:29.330
IN‐HOUSE.
AS IN IN‐HOUSE COUNSEL.

40:29.363 --> 40:31.766
IT'S A LOT MORE
INTERESTING.

40:31.799 --> 40:33.801
LOT LESS BULLSHIT.
[ Clears Throat ]

40:36.103 --> 40:40.441
NOPE. I THINK I'VE DECIDED
TO RETIRE, HUGH.

40:40.474 --> 40:43.077
GET AN R. V.
AND TRAVEL THE COUNTRY.

40:43.110 --> 40:45.079
SINCE WHEN?

40:45.112 --> 40:47.281
SINCE NOW.

40:47.314 --> 40:49.784
[ Gunshots ]

40:49.817 --> 40:53.187
FEELS GOOD, DON'T IT?
WHO IS THAT? DERSHOWITZ?
COME HERE, YOU LIBERAL SCUM.

40:57.324 --> 40:59.293
[ Cael ]
IT STAYS THERE.

40:59.326 --> 41:02.429
[ Di Di Scoffs ]
IT'S 'CAUSE YOUR NOSE
IS BIGGER, YOU WEIRDO.

41:02.463 --> 41:04.498
[ Cael ]
YEAH? YEAH?
[ Di Di Laughs ]

41:06.467 --> 41:08.469
[ Cael ]
HOLD ON.

41:10.572 --> 41:12.574
[ Dahlia ]
OH, YOU'RE JUST IN TIME.

41:15.710 --> 41:18.746
‐ YOU COOKED.
‐ I DID.

41:20.715 --> 41:22.684
AM I HERE?
YEAH.

41:24.586 --> 41:26.888
[ Di Di ]
JUST SIT YOU DOWN.

41:27.922 --> 41:31.325
[ Exhales ]
MAYBE WE SHOULD SAY GRACE?

41:35.496 --> 41:38.499
‐ OKAY.
‐ UH‐‐

41:42.036 --> 41:44.005
BLESS US, O LORD,
AND THESE THY GIFTS,

41:44.038 --> 41:46.340
FOR WHICH WE ARE ABOUT
TO RECEIVE THROUGH
CHRIST OUR LORD, AMEN.

41:46.373 --> 41:48.375
AMEN.
[ Di Di ]
AMEN.

41:52.179 --> 41:54.682
SO, DAD, HOW'D IT GO?

41:54.716 --> 41:57.885
WELL, THE GOOD NEWS IS
I GOT THE JOB.

41:57.919 --> 41:59.754
YOU DID?

41:59.787 --> 42:01.756
[ All Chuckling ]

42:01.789 --> 42:06.093
‐ WELL, WHAT'S THE BAD NEWS?
‐ THE BAD NEWS IS I GOT THE JOB,

42:06.127 --> 42:08.162
AND I DON'T KNOW SHIT
ABOUT THE LAW.

42:08.195 --> 42:12.166
DAD, THERE'S SO MANY BOOKS
ON LAW UPSTAIRS. I CAN HELP YOU
BRUSH UP IF YOU NEED HEL
P.

42:12.199 --> 42:15.436
THAT'S VERY SWEET, BABY, BUT,
UH, YOU GOTTA KNOW SOMETHING
BEFORE YOU CAN BRUSH IT
UP.

42:15.469 --> 42:18.573
‐YOU TALKED YOUR WAY THROUGH THE
NASHVILLE THING. YOU'RE FINE.
‐YEAH.

42:18.606 --> 42:23.511
THAT WAS A MISDEMEANOR.
I CAN'T CON MY WAY
INTO A COURT OF LAW.

42:23.545 --> 42:28.015
A COURT OF LAW IS
A COURT OF GODDAMN LAW.

42:28.049 --> 42:32.386
WHO AM I KIDDING?
I‐‐ I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
A SECURITIES LITIGATOR IS.

42:32.419 --> 42:34.922
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
DON'T KNOW.

42:34.956 --> 42:37.358
I'LL THINK OF SOMETHING.

42:37.391 --> 42:39.894
YEAH. YOU ALWAYS DO.

42:42.597 --> 42:44.632
LEAST WE'VE GOT THE MONEY.

42:44.666 --> 42:47.602
FOR NOW WE CAN USE THAT
TO PAY THE BILLS.

42:51.405 --> 42:53.875
OW! GODDAMN IT!

42:53.908 --> 42:57.211
THIS IS USELESS, WAYNE!
WE ARE NEVER GONNA FIND IT!

42:57.244 --> 43:00.548
TELL ME ONCE AGAIN.
WHICH TREE DID YOU THINK
IT WAS?

43:00.582 --> 43:03.885
I DON'T KNOW.
I WASN'T THINKING STRAIGHT.

43:03.918 --> 43:06.888
‐ YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT, MA?
I WONDER WHY.
‐ WOULD YOU SHUT YOUR MOUTH?

43:06.921 --> 43:10.291
‐ WHY DON'T YOU SHUT YOUR MOUTH?
‐ DAMN IT! THIS IS 40 GRAND!

43:10.324 --> 43:13.595
WE CAN'T GO BACK
HOME NOW, MA.
THAT IS NOT HOME!

43:13.628 --> 43:16.564
THIS IS THE ONLY HOME
WE GOT NOW.

43:16.598 --> 43:20.267
WE COULD PAINT
DRIVEWAYS AGAIN.

43:20.301 --> 43:22.970
WE DON'T HAVE TO LIVE IN SOME
BIG‐ASS HOUSE LIKE THAT, DAD.

43:23.004 --> 43:24.906
[ Dahlia ]
WHAT ARE WE DOIN' HERE,
WAYNE?

43:24.939 --> 43:27.975
WE DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY.

43:28.009 --> 43:30.077
YOU AIN'T NEVER
GONNA BE A LAWYER.

43:30.111 --> 43:33.515
WE'RE TRAVELLERS, BABY.
WE'RE THIEVES.

43:35.116 --> 43:38.986
WE GOTTA STICK WITH
OUR OWN KIND.
WE ARE WITH OUR OWN KIND.

43:39.020 --> 43:41.088
THAT'S WHY WE'RE GONNA
STAY RIGHT HERE.

43:41.122 --> 43:43.457
TOGETHER. US.

43:43.490 --> 43:47.294
I'M GONNA GET US ALL
THE LIFE WE DESERVE,
WHETHER WE WANT IT OR NOT.

43:47.328 --> 43:50.665
‐ WHERE YOU GOIN'?
‐ TO WAR.

44:06.714 --> 44:09.350
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

44:18.693 --> 44:21.128
DOUG.
HUGH.

44:21.162 --> 44:24.398
[ Sniffs ]
ALMOST MIDNIGHT, DOUG.

44:24.431 --> 44:26.400
YOU THE GHOST
OF CHRISTMAS PAST?

44:26.433 --> 44:28.970
YES, I AM.

44:29.003 --> 44:31.338
NICE GUN.
THANK YOU.

44:35.009 --> 44:37.579
WHY ARE YOU
IN MY HOUSE, DOUG?

44:37.612 --> 44:39.647
[ Sighs ]

44:39.681 --> 44:41.683
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

44:43.518 --> 44:46.487
WHY AM I TALKING TO YOU?
[ Clears Throat ]

44:46.521 --> 44:48.590
[ Groans ]

44:48.623 --> 44:51.425
WE'RE DISCUSSING
MY PACKAGE, HUGH.

44:51.458 --> 44:54.696
YOUR WHAT?
MY COMPENSATION PACKAGE.

44:54.729 --> 44:57.732
FOR MY SERVICES.
AS WHAT? MY POOL BOY?

44:57.765 --> 45:00.234
AS YOUR IN‐HOUSE COUNSEL.

45:01.468 --> 45:04.105
I DIDN'T OFFER YOU A JOB.

45:04.138 --> 45:06.340
‐ I THINK YOU DID.
‐ IS THAT RIGHT?

45:06.373 --> 45:10.545
I'M WORTH 150 MILLION
ON PAPER, DOUG.

45:10.578 --> 45:15.617
I RUN PANCO.
I RUN TECHCURRENTS.
I RUN A LOT OF THINGS.

45:15.650 --> 45:18.720
NOT BAD FOR A GUY WHO USED TO
CLEAN SEPTIC TANKS, HUH?

45:18.753 --> 45:23.357
SO, YOU WANT A SHOT TO BE
MY IN‐HOUSE COUNSEL,

45:23.390 --> 45:25.960
YOU GOTTA BE THE BEST.

45:25.993 --> 45:29.030
'CAUSE I WIPE MY ASS WITH
THOSE HAYDEN‐JAVITZ PRICKS.

45:29.063 --> 45:31.933
YOU UNDERSTAND?
SO, ARE YOU THE BEST, DOUG?

45:33.000 --> 45:35.970
OR ARE YOU JUST MIDDLIN'?

45:36.003 --> 45:38.005
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
I TELL YOU WHAT I THINK.

45:39.741 --> 45:42.710
I THINK YOU'RE AN ASSHOLE, HUGH.

45:42.744 --> 45:45.713
[ Laughing ]
YOU REALLY ARE.

45:45.747 --> 45:48.916
AND YOUR NUMBERS‐‐
THEY'RE NOT THAT HIGH.

45:52.687 --> 45:55.289
YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE.
IT'S NORMAL.

46:02.429 --> 46:05.600
I THINK YOU SIMPLY
LIKE TO SHOOT YOUR FRIENDS
AND NEIGHBORS IN THE FACE.

46:08.670 --> 46:10.304
PUT DOWN MY GUN.

46:10.337 --> 46:14.609
NOW, I KNOW THIS BECAUSE
I USE MY POWERS OF DEDUCTION.

46:14.642 --> 46:18.312
I ASSESS AND DEDUCE.

46:18.345 --> 46:20.582
IT'S WHAT A GOOD LAWYER
DOES, HUGH.

46:20.615 --> 46:23.785
HE ASSESSES AND DEDUCES.

46:23.818 --> 46:25.820
A GOOD LAWYER...

46:25.853 --> 46:29.123
MAKES YOU BELIEVE THE TRUTH.

46:34.295 --> 46:36.263
HOLY SHIT.

46:36.297 --> 46:38.332
BUT, HUGH‐‐
[ Exhales Deeply ]

46:38.365 --> 46:40.535
YOU KNOW WHAT
A GREAT LAWYER DOES?

46:40.568 --> 46:42.303
DOUG. WHOA.
A GREAT LAWYER...

46:42.336 --> 46:46.140
MAKES YOU BELIEVE THE LIE.

46:48.876 --> 46:52.814
[ Clicks ]
OH, SHIT.

47:06.327 --> 47:08.495
AH.

47:11.098 --> 47:13.134
[ Chuckles ]

47:13.167 --> 47:16.671
‐ YOU CRAZY BASTARD.
‐ THANK YOU.

47:23.545 --> 47:25.580
YOU'RE A SICK MOTHER, DOUG.

47:25.613 --> 47:29.016
YES. YES, I AM.

47:36.390 --> 47:38.425
AND I LIKE THAT IN A LIAR.

47:40.862 --> 47:43.665
[ Wheezing Laugh ]

47:43.698 --> 47:46.167
[ Squealing ]

47:46.200 --> 47:48.502
WHOO! WHOO‐HOO!

47:48.536 --> 47:50.838
HEY, BABY.
DON'T SPLASH MOMMY.

47:50.872 --> 47:56.010
BABY, YOU REALLY GONNA
GET PAID $200,000 A YEAR?

47:56.043 --> 47:59.013
‐ $200,000.
‐ WITH BENEFITS!

47:59.046 --> 48:01.983
[ Wayne ]
WITH BENEFITS!
[ All Laughing ]

48:02.984 --> 48:04.952
YEAH!
[ Wayne ]
UH‐OH.

48:04.986 --> 48:06.954
[ Dahlia ]
WHAT?
I GOTTA PEE.

48:06.988 --> 48:09.256
OH, MY GOD.
I GOTTA PEE.

48:09.290 --> 48:12.093
YOU CAN'T PEE
IN THE POOL, DAD.
WE'RE BUFFERS NOW.

48:12.126 --> 48:14.862
WE DON'T SWIM
IN THE TOILET.
Y'ALL CAN'T PISS IN OUR POOL.

48:14.896 --> 48:16.864
I AM A SHARK.

48:16.898 --> 48:19.266
I GOT $200,000.

48:19.300 --> 48:21.502
DON'T PEE IN THE POOL.
[ Squeals ]
DAD, NO!

48:24.238 --> 48:26.574
[ Di Di ]
DON'T GET IN HERE. IT'S HOT.
[ Buzzing ]

48:29.076 --> 48:31.078
[ Chattering ]

48:34.616 --> 48:36.851
[ Di Di ]
DON'T COME IN HERE. IT'S HOT.

48:38.119 --> 48:40.121
[ Chattering Continues ]

48:42.256 --> 48:44.258
[ Buzzing Continues ]

48:49.463 --> 48:51.465
[ Chattering ]

48:53.334 --> 48:56.103
[ Buzzing Continues ]

48:57.271 --> 48:59.306
[ Beeps ]

48:59.340 --> 49:01.576
[ Chattering ]
[ Woman On Phone ]
DOUG?

49:01.609 --> 49:04.345
I KNOW YOU'RE THERE.

49:04.378 --> 49:07.081
SAY SOMETHIN'.

49:07.114 --> 49:09.150
DON'T YOU HANG UP
ON ME, DOUG.

